      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0643P0-04593'>
        <a name='S5LV0643P0_20030127_GCR_70'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-clinton-davis' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0643P0_20030127_GCR_70' title='Link to this speech by Mr Clinton Davis' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-clinton-davis" title="Mr Clinton Davis">Lord Clinton-Davis</a></cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            I support the argument advanced by the noble Lord, Lord Renton&#x2014;not for the first time. The situation at present is left at large. That is not satisfactory from the point of view of the banks, or from the point of view of the person who is affected by the notice. My noble friend the Minister
            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_130gc' title='Col. 130GC &mdash; HL Deb 27 January 2003 vol 643 c130GC' name='column_130gc' href='#column_130gc' rel='bookmark'>130GC</a>
            ought to consider some appropriate provision between now and Report. This is far too important a matter to leave.
          </p>
